My highest-confidence prediction

If Pantheon keeps evolving along its current trajectory, it will eventually stop being organized around named doctrines altogether.

Instead, every doctrine will become an instance of a small algebra.

Something like:

* Preserve
* Distinguish
* Compress
* Expand
* Translate
* Compose
* Perturb
* Reconstruct
* Validate
* Route
* Synchronize
* Learn

Then the named operators—Spider, Mirror, Kurage, Checksum, Rosetta, Pinecone, Flood Eater—become memorable, human-scale embodiments of those primitives rather than independent concepts.

That would close a loop that has been present since the earliest “Garden” and “Money Bin” ideas through the middle-stage emphasis on continuity, signaling, and second-pass meaning, all the way to the recent focus on invariants, reconstruction, and the Continuity Kernel. The mythology becomes the user interface; the operator algebra becomes the engine; the invariants become the physics. That’s a remarkably coherent arc.